-- Zimbabwe’s TN Holdings to Open Supermarkets, Herald Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-01-05T06:42:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/zimbabwe-s-tn-holdings-to-open-supermarkets-herald-reports.html
TN Holdings Ltd. (TEDCO)  will open
supermarkets and fast food outlets in  Zimbabwe ’s capital,
Harare, after signing a 12-year lease on 25 outlets owned by
Rufaro Marketing (Pvt) Ltd., a company owned by the city
council, the  Herald  newspaper reported.  TN will invest $2.5 million before opening its first
supermarket in Harare’s city center in February, the Herald
said, citing Chief Executive Officer Tawanda Nyambirai.  TN Holdings has 24 banking branches, electrical and
clothing retailers and furniture manufacturing businesses in
Zimbabwe, the Herald said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
